sec.p:
ADC (1) and ADCi (2) were calculated according to the following equations:(1)ADC (%)=100−[100×(Id/If×Nf/Nd)] (1), (2)ADCi (%)=ADCdt+[ADCdt−ADCref)×(r×Nref/i×Ni)] (2), in which (1)
ADC is the apparent digestibility coefficient;
Id is chromic oxide’s concentration in the diet (%);
If is chromic oxide’s concentration in the feces (%);
Nd is the nutrient’s concentration in the diet (%);
Nf is the nutrient’s concentration in the feces (%);(2)
ADCi is the nutrient’s apparent digestibility coefficient in the test ingredient;
ADCdt is the nutrient’s apparent digestibility coefficient in the test diet;
ADCref is the nutrient’s apparent digestibility coefficient in the reference diet;
r is the reference diet’s proportion in the test diet (0.6994);
i is the test ingredient’s proportion in the test diet (0.3);
Nref is the nutrient’s concentration in the reference diet (% as fed);
Ni is the nutrient’s concentration in the ingredient (% as fed).
